by .Pitt’s Best Buddies organization.

The organization, begun in 1987 by
John F. Kennedy’s nephew Anthony Shriver,

matches an intellectually disabled person 1

with a Pitt student who has similar interests.

The intellectually disabled can hear
about Best Buddies through their casework-
ers, or through Best Buddies’ community
partnerships with organizations like Family

The goal of the program is as simple as
offering friendship to those who have a hard
time ﬁnding it on their own.

“The problem is a lot of [the intellectu-
ally disabled] get ridiculed because of their
disabilities,” said Aaron Probst, co-president
ofBestBuddies. ..  , , _

Matched “buddies” can form lasting
ﬁiendships by getting together to go bowl-
ing, eat lunch or do other fun things, said
Probst, dressed in army fatigues and combat
boots. ’

Mike Long, aka. Superman, met his
